{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"I remember the very first time\nI went to a nice restaurant,"},{"time":3719,"text":"a really nice restaurant."},{"time":5360,"text":"It was for a law firm recruitment dinner,"},{"time":7520,"text":"and I remember beforehand\nthe waitress walked around"},{"time":10000,"text":"and asked whether we wanted some wine,"},{"time":11880,"text":"so I said, \"Sure,\nI'll take some white wine.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":14800,"text":"And she immediately said,"},{"time":16560,"text":"\"Would you like sauvignon blanc\nor chardonnay?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":19680,"text":"And I remember thinking,"},{"time":21640,"text":"\"Come on, lady,\nstop with the fancy French words"},{"time":24520,"text":"and just give me some white wine.\""},{"time":27400,"text":"But I used my powers of deduction"},{"time":29040,"text":"and recognized that chardonnay\nand sauvignon blanc"},{"time":31480,"text":"were two separate types of white wine,"},{"time":33400,"text":"and so I told her\nthat I would take the chardonnay,"},{"time":35840,"text":"because frankly that was\nthe easiest one to pronounce for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39960,"text":"So I had a lot of experiences like that"},{"time":42080,"text":"during my first couple of years\nas a law student at Yale,"},{"time":45480,"text":"because, despite all outward appearances,\nI'm a cultural outsider."},{"time":49240,"text":"I didn't come from the elites."},{"time":50840,"text":"I didn't come from the Northeast\nor from San Francisco."},{"time":55200,"text":"I came from a southern Ohio steel town,"},{"time":57320,"text":"and it's a town that's really\nstruggling in a lot of ways,"},{"time":60080,"text":"ways that are indicative\nof the broader struggles"},{"time":62560,"text":"of America's working class."},{"time":64720,"text":"Heroin has moved in,"},{"time":66080,"text":"killing a lot of people, people I know."},{"time":68680,"text":"Family violence, domestic violence,\nand divorce have torn apart families."},{"time":73400,"text":"And there's a very unique\nsense of pessimism that's moved in."},{"time":77600,"text":"Think about rising mortality rates\nin these communities"},{"time":80240,"text":"and recognize that\nfor a lot of these folks,"},{"time":82440,"text":"the problems that they're seeing"},{"time":84040,"text":"are actually causing rising death rates\nin their own communities,"},{"time":87760,"text":"so there's a very real sense of struggle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91160,"text":"I had a very front-row seat\nto that struggle."},{"time":93720,"text":"My family has been part of that struggle\nfor a very long time."},{"time":99080,"text":"I come from a family\nthat doesn't have a whole lot of money."},{"time":103440,"text":"The addiction that plagued my community"},{"time":105880,"text":"also plagued my family,\nand even, sadly, my own mom."},{"time":109760,"text":"There were a lot of problems\nthat I saw in my own family,"},{"time":113920,"text":"problems caused sometimes\nby a lack of money,"},{"time":116800,"text":"problems caused sometimes by a lack\nof access to resources and social capital"},{"time":121160,"text":"that really affected my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124400,"text":"If you had looked at my life\nwhen I was 14 years old"},{"time":127200,"text":"and said, \"Well, what's going\nto happen to this kid?\""},{"time":130280,"text":"you would have concluded\nthat I would have struggled"},{"time":133160,"text":"with what academics call upward mobility."},{"time":136560,"text":"So upward mobility is an abstract term,"},{"time":139560,"text":"but it strikes at something\nthat's very core"},{"time":142320,"text":"at the heart of the American Dream."},{"time":144040,"text":"It's the sense,"},{"time":145280,"text":"and it measures whether kids like me"},{"time":147080,"text":"who grow up in poor communities\nare going to live a better life,"},{"time":150120,"text":"whether they're going to have a chance\nto live a materially better existence,"},{"time":155520,"text":"or whether they're going to stay\nin the circumstances where they came from."},{"time":159080,"text":"And one of the things\nwe've learned, unfortunately,"},{"time":161520,"text":"is that upward mobility isn't as high\nas we'd like it to be in this country,"},{"time":165480,"text":"and interestingly,\nit's very geographically distributed."},{"time":170080,"text":"So take Utah, for instance."},{"time":172840,"text":"In Utah a poor kid is actually doing OK,"},{"time":176400,"text":"very likely to live their share\nand their part in the American Dream."},{"time":180560,"text":"But if you think of where I'm from,"},{"time":182440,"text":"in the South, in Appalachia,\nin southern Ohio,"},{"time":186400,"text":"it's very unlikely\nthat kids like that will rise."},{"time":190640,"text":"The American Dream\nin those parts of the country"},{"time":192920,"text":"is in a very real sense just a dream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195960,"text":"So why is that happening?"},{"time":198120,"text":"So one reason is obviously\neconomic or structural."},{"time":200960,"text":"So you think of these areas."},{"time":202520,"text":"They're beset by these\nterrible economic trends,"},{"time":205160,"text":"built around industries\nlike coal and steel"},{"time":207800,"text":"that make it harder\nfor folks to get ahead."},{"time":210320,"text":"That's certainly one problem."},{"time":211920,"text":"There's also the problem of brain drain,\nwhere the really talented people,"},{"time":215440,"text":"because they can't find\nhigh-skilled work at home,"},{"time":217840,"text":"end up moving elsewhere,"},{"time":219120,"text":"so they don't build a business\nor non-profit where they're from,"},{"time":222160,"text":"they end up going elsewhere\nand taking their talents with them."},{"time":225160,"text":"There are failing schools\nin a lot of these communities,"},{"time":227840,"text":"failing to give kids\nthe educational leg up"},{"time":229920,"text":"that really makes it possible for kids\nto have opportunities later in life."},{"time":233480,"text":"These things are all important."},{"time":235040,"text":"I don't mean to discount\nthese structural barriers."},{"time":237480,"text":"But when I look back at my life\nand my community,"},{"time":239840,"text":"something else was going on,\nsomething else mattered."},{"time":243840,"text":"It's difficult to quantify,\nbut it was no less real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248120,"text":"So for starters, there was\na very real sense of hopelessness"},{"time":251800,"text":"in the community that I grew up in."},{"time":253600,"text":"There was a sense that kids had\nthat their choices didn't matter."},{"time":256760,"text":"No matter what happened,\nno matter how hard they worked,"},{"time":259440,"text":"no matter how hard\nthey tried to get ahead,"},{"time":261560,"text":"nothing good would happen."},{"time":264160,"text":"So that's a tough feeling\nto grow up around."},{"time":267240,"text":"That's a tough mindset to penetrate,"},{"time":270440,"text":"and it leads sometimes\nto very conspiratorial places."},{"time":275240,"text":"So let's just take one\npolitical issue that's pretty hot,"},{"time":279200,"text":"affirmative action."},{"time":280720,"text":"So depending on your politics,\nyou might think that affirmative action"},{"time":284040,"text":"is either a wise or an unwise way\nto promote diversity in the workplace"},{"time":287440,"text":"or the classroom."},{"time":288760,"text":"But if you grow up in an area like this,"},{"time":290800,"text":"you see affirmative action\nas a tool to hold people like you back."},{"time":294560,"text":"That's especially true if you're\na member of the white working class."},{"time":297840,"text":"You see it as something\nthat isn't just about good or bad policy."},{"time":301280,"text":"You see it as something\nthat's actively conspiring,"},{"time":304000,"text":"where people with political\nand financial power"},{"time":306280,"text":"are working against you."},{"time":307920,"text":"And there are a lot of ways that you see\nthat conspiracy against you --"},{"time":313520,"text":"perceived, real, but it's there,"},{"time":316440,"text":"and it warps expectations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319040,"text":"So if you think about what do you do\nwhen you grow up in that world,"},{"time":322280,"text":"you can respond in a couple of ways."},{"time":324040,"text":"One, you can say,\n\"I'm not going to work hard,"},{"time":326240,"text":"because no matter how hard I work,\nit's not going to matter.\""},{"time":329160,"text":"Another thing you might do is say,"},{"time":330840,"text":"\"Well, I'm not going to go\nafter the traditional markers of success,"},{"time":334080,"text":"like a university education\nor a prestigious job,"},{"time":336440,"text":"because the people who care\nabout those things are unlike me."},{"time":339360,"text":"They're never going to let me in.\""},{"time":341004,"text":"When I got admitted to Yale,\na family member asked me"},{"time":343505,"text":"if I had pretended to be a liberal\nto get by the admissions committee."},{"time":346840,"text":"Seriously."},{"time":348640,"text":"And it's obviously not the case\nthat there was a liberal box to check"},{"time":352680,"text":"on the application,"},{"time":354200,"text":"but it speaks to a very real\ninsecurity in these places"},{"time":357880,"text":"that you have to pretend\nto be somebody you're not"},{"time":360280,"text":"to get past these various social barriers."},{"time":363080,"text":"It's a very significant problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365640,"text":"Even if you don't give in\nto that hopelessness,"},{"time":368080,"text":"even if you think, let's say,"},{"time":369920,"text":"that your choices matter\nand you want to make the good choices,"},{"time":373560,"text":"you want to do better\nfor yourself and for your family,"},{"time":376480,"text":"it's sometimes hard\nto even know what those choices are"},{"time":379680,"text":"when you grow up\nin a community like I did."},{"time":381800,"text":"I didn't know, for example,"},{"time":383440,"text":"that you had to go\nto law school to be a lawyer."},{"time":386360,"text":"I didn't know that elite universities,\nas research consistently tells us,"},{"time":390320,"text":"are cheaper for low-income kids"},{"time":392120,"text":"because these universities\nhave bigger endowments,"},{"time":394720,"text":"can offer more generous financial aid."},{"time":396920,"text":"I remember I learned this"},{"time":398200,"text":"when I got the financial aid letter\nfrom Yale for myself,"},{"time":401040,"text":"tens of thousands of dollars\nin need-based aid,"},{"time":403760,"text":"which is a term I had never heard before."},{"time":405920,"text":"But I turned to my aunt\nwhen I got that letter and said,"},{"time":408600,"text":"\"You know, I think this just means\nthat for the first time in my life,"},{"time":411920,"text":"being poor has paid really well.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":415360,"text":"So I didn't have access\nto that information"},{"time":418200,"text":"because the social networks around me\ndidn't have access to that information."},{"time":421880,"text":"I learned from my community\nhow to shoot a gun, how to shoot it well."},{"time":425560,"text":"I learned how to make\na damn good biscuit recipe."},{"time":428040,"text":"The trick, by the way,\nis frozen butter, not warm butter."},{"time":432080,"text":"But I didn't learn how to get ahead."},{"time":434000,"text":"I didn't learn how to make\nthe good decisions"},{"time":436600,"text":"about education and opportunity"},{"time":438480,"text":"that you need to make"},{"time":441200,"text":"to actually have a chance\nin this 21st century knowledge economy."},{"time":444400,"text":"Economists call the value\nthat we gain from our informal networks,"},{"time":448560,"text":"from our friends and colleagues\nand family \"social capital.\""},{"time":452200,"text":"The social capital that I had\nwasn't built for 21st century America,"},{"time":456040,"text":"and it showed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458360,"text":"There's something else\nthat's really important that's going on"},{"time":461320,"text":"that our community\ndoesn't like to talk about,"},{"time":463520,"text":"but it's very real."},{"time":465120,"text":"Working-class kids are much more likely"},{"time":467040,"text":"to face what's called\nadverse childhood experiences,"},{"time":469800,"text":"which is just a fancy word\nfor childhood trauma:"},{"time":474280,"text":"getting hit or yelled at,\nput down by a parent repeatedly,"},{"time":477880,"text":"watching someone hit or beat your parent,"},{"time":480320,"text":"watching someone do drugs\nor abuse alcohol."},{"time":483720,"text":"These are all instances\nof childhood trauma,"},{"time":486280,"text":"and they're pretty\ncommonplace in my family."},{"time":488960,"text":"Importantly, they're not just\ncommonplace in my family right now."},{"time":492400,"text":"They're also multigenerational."},{"time":494440,"text":"So my grandparents,"},{"time":496640,"text":"the very first time that they had kids,"},{"time":499440,"text":"they expected that they\nwere going to raise them in a way"},{"time":502160,"text":"that was uniquely good."},{"time":503800,"text":"They were middle class,"},{"time":505080,"text":"they were able to earn\na good wage in a steel mill."},{"time":507485,"text":"But what ended up happening"},{"time":508840,"text":"is that they exposed their kids\nto a lot of the childhood trauma"},{"time":511880,"text":"that had gone back many generations."},{"time":514600,"text":"My mom was 12 when she saw\nmy grandma set my grandfather on fire."},{"time":520120,"text":"His crime was that he came home drunk"},{"time":522960,"text":"after she told him,"},{"time":524200,"text":"\"If you come home drunk,\nI'm gonna kill you.\""},{"time":527240,"text":"And she tried to do it."},{"time":529440,"text":"Think about the way\nthat that affects a child's mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533520,"text":"And we think of these things\nas especially rare,"},{"time":536480,"text":"but a study by the Wisconsin\nChildren's Trust Fund found"},{"time":540480,"text":"that 40 percent of low-income kids face\nmultiple instances of childhood trauma,"},{"time":546800,"text":"compared to only 29 percent\nfor upper-income kids."},{"time":550120,"text":"And think about what that really means."},{"time":552800,"text":"If you're a low-income kid,"},{"time":554560,"text":"almost half of you face multiple\ninstances of childhood trauma."},{"time":559040,"text":"This is not an isolated problem."},{"time":560880,"text":"This is a very significant issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563800,"text":"We know what happens\nto the kids who experience that life."},{"time":567920,"text":"They're more likely to do drugs,\nmore likely to go to jail,"},{"time":571240,"text":"more likely to drop out of high school,"},{"time":573560,"text":"and most importantly,"},{"time":575000,"text":"they're more likely\nto do to their children"},{"time":577240,"text":"what their parents did to them."},{"time":579640,"text":"This trauma, this chaos in the home,"},{"time":582760,"text":"is our culture's\nvery worst gift to our children,"},{"time":586240,"text":"and it's a gift that keeps on giving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590280,"text":"So you combine all that,"},{"time":592120,"text":"the hopelessness, the despair,"},{"time":594840,"text":"the cynicism about the future,"},{"time":597200,"text":"the childhood trauma,"},{"time":599440,"text":"the low social capital,"},{"time":601360,"text":"and you begin to understand why me,"},{"time":603680,"text":"at the age of 14,"},{"time":605280,"text":"was ready to become\njust another statistic,"},{"time":607640,"text":"another kid who failed to beat the odds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610640,"text":"But something unexpected happened."},{"time":613360,"text":"I did beat the odds."},{"time":615120,"text":"Things turned up for me."},{"time":617280,"text":"I graduated from high school,\nfrom college, I went to law school,"},{"time":621040,"text":"and I have a pretty good job now."},{"time":623320,"text":"So what happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":625320,"text":"Well, one thing that happened\nis that my grandparents,"},{"time":627880,"text":"the same grandparents\nof setting someone on fire fame,"},{"time":630440,"text":"they really shaped up\nby the time I came around."},{"time":633320,"text":"They provided me a stable home,"},{"time":636400,"text":"a stable family."},{"time":637720,"text":"They made sure"},{"time":638960,"text":"that when my parents weren't able\nto do the things that kids need,"},{"time":642120,"text":"they stepped in and filled that role."},{"time":644880,"text":"My grandma especially\ndid two things that really matter."},{"time":647560,"text":"One, she provided that peaceful home\nthat allowed me to focus on homework"},{"time":651080,"text":"and the things that kids\nshould be focused on."},{"time":653720,"text":"But she was also\nthis incredibly perceptive woman,"},{"time":656120,"text":"despite not even having\na middle school education."},{"time":658520,"text":"She recognized the message\nthat my community had for me,"},{"time":661200,"text":"that my choices didn't matter,"},{"time":663280,"text":"that the deck was stacked against me."},{"time":665120,"text":"She once told me,"},{"time":666360,"text":"\"JD, never be like those losers who think\nthe deck is stacked against them."},{"time":670360,"text":"You can do anything you want to.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":672720,"text":"And yet she recognized\nthat life wasn't fair."},{"time":675960,"text":"It's hard to strike that balance,"},{"time":677600,"text":"to tell a kid that life isn't fair,"},{"time":679640,"text":"but also recognize and enforce in them\nthe reality that their choices matter."},{"time":684920,"text":"But mamaw was able\nto strike that balance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689040,"text":"The other thing that really helped\nwas the United States Marine Corps."},{"time":692360,"text":"So we think of the Marine Corps\nas a military outfit, and of course it is,"},{"time":695880,"text":"but for me, the US Marine Corps\nwas a four-year crash course"},{"time":698760,"text":"in character education."},{"time":700000,"text":"It taught me how to make a bed,\nhow to do laundry,"},{"time":702400,"text":"how to wake up early,\nhow to manage my finances."},{"time":704680,"text":"These are things\nmy community didn't teach me."},{"time":706880,"text":"I remember when I went\nto go buy a car for the very first time,"},{"time":709857,"text":"I was offered a dealer's\nlow, low interest rate of 21.9 percent,"},{"time":714200,"text":"and I was ready\nto sign on the dotted line."},{"time":717680,"text":"But I didn't take that deal,"},{"time":719560,"text":"because I went and took it to my officer"},{"time":721600,"text":"who told me, \"Stop being an idiot,"},{"time":723760,"text":"go to the local credit union,\nand get a better deal.\""},{"time":726280,"text":"And so that's what I did."},{"time":727760,"text":"But without the Marine Corps,"},{"time":729200,"text":"I would have never had access\nto that knowledge."},{"time":731480,"text":"I would have had\na financial calamity, frankly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734720,"text":"The last thing I want to say\nis that I had a lot of good fortune"},{"time":737880,"text":"in the mentors and people"},{"time":739480,"text":"who have played\nan important role in my life."},{"time":741640,"text":"From the Marines,\nfrom Ohio State, from Yale,"},{"time":744720,"text":"from other places,"},{"time":746000,"text":"people have really stepped in"},{"time":747680,"text":"and ensured that they filled\nthat social capital gap"},{"time":750520,"text":"that it was pretty obvious,\napparently, that I had."},{"time":753480,"text":"That comes from good fortune,"},{"time":755840,"text":"but a lot of children\naren't going to have that good fortune,"},{"time":759160,"text":"and I think that raises\nreally important questions for all of us"},{"time":762880,"text":"about how we're going to change that."},{"time":765600,"text":"We need to ask questions about\nhow we're going to give low-income kids"},{"time":769600,"text":"who come from a broken home\naccess to a loving home."},{"time":773160,"text":"We need to ask questions"},{"time":774440,"text":"about how we're going\nto teach low-income parents"},{"time":776800,"text":"how to better interact\nwith their children,"},{"time":778960,"text":"with their partners."},{"time":780480,"text":"We need to ask questions\nabout how we give social capital,"},{"time":784960,"text":"mentorship to low-income kids\nwho don't have it."},{"time":788360,"text":"We need to think about\nhow we teach working class children"},{"time":791440,"text":"about not just hard skills,"},{"time":793960,"text":"like reading, mathematics,"},{"time":796080,"text":"but also soft skills,"},{"time":797440,"text":"like conflict resolution\nand financial management."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801440,"text":"Now, I don't have all of the answers."},{"time":804680,"text":"I don't know all of the solutions\nto this problem,"},{"time":808360,"text":"but I do know this:"},{"time":810600,"text":"in southern Ohio right now,"},{"time":812360,"text":"there's a kid who is\nanxiously awaiting their dad,"},{"time":816160,"text":"wondering whether,\nwhen he comes through the door,"},{"time":818560,"text":"he'll walk calmly or stumble drunkly."},{"time":822000,"text":"There's a kid"},{"time":824560,"text":"whose mom sticks a needle in her arm"},{"time":826920,"text":"and passes out,"},{"time":828440,"text":"and he doesn't know\nwhy she doesn't cook him dinner,"},{"time":831360,"text":"and he goes to bed hungry that night."},{"time":834400,"text":"There's a kid who has\nno hope for the future"},{"time":838360,"text":"but desperately\nwants to live a better life."},{"time":841640,"text":"They just want somebody\nto show it to them."},{"time":844680,"text":"I don't have all the answers,"},{"time":846560,"text":"but I know that unless our society\nstarts asking better questions"},{"time":851520,"text":"about why I was so lucky"},{"time":853640,"text":"and about how to get that luck\nto more of our communities"},{"time":856720,"text":"and our country's children,"},{"time":858400,"text":"we're going to continue\nto have a very significant problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861680,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862920,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}